	        Send us your pictures   ·  Send us your stories Police have opened a murder investigation after a teenage boy was found dead near a cemetery in Pampierstad, Northern Cape. A passer-by alerted the police after he discovered the body behind the Pampierstad Cemetery on Thursday, police spokesperson Captain Sergio Kock said. "The deceased was found on the ground with a bicycle chain around his neck." Anyone with information about the incident or the suspect should call Sergeant Lebogang Tobolo on 073 763 2015.  24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.  